  parity-based extended mind theories, arguing that cognitive extension
  occurs through the integration of neural, bodily, and environmental
  resources into hybrid systems via cognitive practices. Rather than
  external resources functionally equivalent to internal ones, integration
  involves complementarity where different resources make distinct
  contributions. Enculturation plays a key role, as cognitive practices are
  culturally transmitted and transform individual cognitive capacities
  through developmental scaffolding.

